BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hubert-training-20260601@training-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260519T074603Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260601
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260602
SUMMARY:Upper Strength + Fueling Focus
DESCRIPTION:Macros: 3250 kcal\, 160 g protein\, 445 g carbs\, 90 g fat\nCa
 tegory: gym\nRun volume: 0 km\nAdjustments:\n- Shortened for schedule con
 straints.\nPlan:\n- Warm-up: 5-8 min easy bike or incline walk\, band pul
 l-aparts\, scap push-ups\, and 2-3 bench ramp sets.\n- Bench press: 4 x 4
 -6 at a conservative post-marathon load\; stop with 1-2 reps in reserve.\
 n- Incline dumbbell press: 3 x 8-10.\n- Seated dumbbell shoulder press: 3
  x 6-10.\n- Cable fly or pec deck: 2-3 x 12-15.\n- Lateral raises: 4 x 12
 -20.\n- Triceps pushdown: 3 x 10-15.\n- Overhead triceps extension: 2 x 1
 2-15.\n- Fueling: keep carbs high at lunch and include a carb-focused pre
 -gym meal 2-3 hours before training.\n- Use the minimum effective dose if
  time or energy is limited: first 3 main lifts\, then leave.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hubert-training-20260602@training-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260519T074603Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260602
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260603
SUMMARY:Lower Strength + Knee Capacity
DESCRIPTION:Macros: 3250 kcal\, 160 g protein\, 445 g carbs\, 90 g fat\nCa
 tegory: gym\nRun volume: 0 km\nAdjustments:\n- Shortened for schedule con
 straints.\nPlan:\n- Warm-up: 8-10 min bike\, ankle rocks\, hip airplanes\
 , bodyweight squats\, and light sled or leg extension if available.\n- Ha
 ck squat: 4 x 6-10\, smooth depth and no grinding.\n- Leg press: 3 x 8-12
 .\n- Romanian deadlift: 4 x 6-8.\n- Bulgarian split squat: 2-3 x 8-10 per
  leg\, controlled tempo.\n- Leg curl: 3 x 10-15.\n- Calf raises: 4 x 10-2
 0.\n- Tibialis raises: 3 x 15-25.\n- Squat skill: goblet squat 3 x 8 plus
  pause bodyweight squat 2 x 8.\n- Fueling: add a salty carb source pre-li
 ft\; this is not a low-carb day.\n- Use the minimum effective dose if tim
 e or energy is limited: first 3 main lifts\, then leave.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hubert-training-20260603@training-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260519T074603Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260603
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260604
SUMMARY:Recovery + Easy Zone 2
DESCRIPTION:Macros: 3250 kcal\, 160 g protein\, 445 g carbs\, 90 g fat\nCa
 tegory: easy_run\nRun volume: 5 km\nPlan:\n- Easy run: 5 km at conversati
 onal effort\, roughly 5:30-6:10/km.\n- Keep cadence light and stop if kne
 es feel worse as the run continues.\n- Mobility: 8-10 min hips\, quads\, 
 calves\, ankles.\n- Fueling: do not run fasted if you feel flat\; fruit o
 r bread plus caffeine is enough before an easy morning run.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hubert-training-20260604@training-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260519T074603Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260604
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260605
SUMMARY:Upper Hypertrophy + Arms/Delts
DESCRIPTION:Macros: 3250 kcal\, 160 g protein\, 445 g carbs\, 90 g fat\nCa
 tegory: gym\nRun volume: 0 km\nAdjustments:\n- Shortened for schedule con
 straints.\nPlan:\n- Warm-up: 5 min easy cardio\, shoulder circles\, light
  rows\, and two easy pressing ramp sets.\n- Weighted pull-ups or bodyweig
 ht pull-ups: 4 x 5-8.\n- Chest-supported row or barbell row: 4 x 6-10.\n-
  Incline dumbbell press: 3 x 8-12.\n- Lat pulldown: 3 x 8-12.\n- Cable ro
 w: 3 x 10-12.\n- Rear delt fly: 3 x 15-20.\n- Lateral raises: 3 x 15-20.\
 n- Curls superset triceps pressdown: 3 x 10-15 each.\n- Core: Pallof pres
 s 3 x 10-12 per side.\n- Fueling: dinner should include protein plus a la
 rge carb portion after training.\n- Use the minimum effective dose if tim
 e or energy is limited: first 3 main lifts\, then leave.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hubert-training-20260605@training-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260519T074603Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260605
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260606
SUMMARY:Lower Posterior Chain + Squat Skill
DESCRIPTION:Macros: 3250 kcal\, 160 g protein\, 445 g carbs\, 90 g fat\nCa
 tegory: gym\nRun volume: 0 km\nPlan:\n- Warm-up: 8 min bike\, dynamic ham
 strings\, glute bridges\, ankle mobility\, and light hinge ramp sets.\n- 
 Romanian deadlift: 4 x 6-8.\n- Hip thrust or glute bridge: 3 x 8-12.\n- F
 ront-foot elevated split squat: 3 x 8-10 per leg\, knee tracking cleanly.
 \n- Seated or lying leg curl: 3 x 10-15.\n- Back extension: 2-3 x 10-15.\
 n- Calf raises: 4 x 10-20.\n- Squat skill: goblet squat 3 x 8\, slow ecce
 ntric and stable foot pressure.\n- If social plans or alcohol are likely\
 , train earlier and keep 1-2 reps in reserve.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hubert-training-20260606@training-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260519T074603Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260606
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260607
SUMMARY:Controlled Hill Sprints + Mobility
DESCRIPTION:Macros: 3250 kcal\, 160 g protein\, 445 g carbs\, 90 g fat\nCa
 tegory: sprint\nRun volume: 3 km\nPlan:\n- Warm-up jog: 3 km total includ
 ing cooldown\, all easy.\n- Dynamic drills: leg swings\, A-skips\, anklin
 g\, high knees\, and 3 relaxed strides.\n- Hill sprints: 6 x 10-12 sec up
 hill at powerful but controlled effort\; full walk-back recovery.\n- Stop
  the sprint set if mechanics get sloppy or knees feel sharp.\n- Accessory
  option: farmer carries 4 x 30-40 m and ab wheel 3 x 6-10.\n- Fueling: ha
 ve carbs before the session and hydrate with electrolytes if sleep was po
 or.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:hubert-training-20260607@training-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260519T074603Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260607
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260608
SUMMARY:Easy Longer Aerobic Run
DESCRIPTION:Macros: 3250 kcal\, 160 g protein\, 445 g carbs\, 90 g fat\nCa
 tegory: long_run\nRun volume: 10 km\nPlan:\n- Easy longer run: 10 km at c
 onversational effort\, roughly 5:15-5:55/km.\n- This is not a race. Keep 
 the final 2 km controlled unless recovery feels excellent.\n- Post-run: p
 rotein plus a large carb meal within 2 hours.\n- Mobility: calves\, quads
 \, hip flexors\, and gentle knee-friendly range work.\n- Fueling: eat car
 bs the night before and before the run\; add electrolytes if warm.
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
